<td id="title_text"><h1><a title="CCD Scanner" class="currentChild" href="CCD_Scanner">CCD Scanner</a></h1></td>



</tr></table>
</td>
</tr></table></div>



<div id="content" class="content wikipage" lang="en" dir="ltr">
<p id="l1">
In imaging, a <a title="Scanner" href="Scanner">scanner</a> containing a <a title="CCD Array" href="CCD_Array">CCD array</a> rather than <a title="Photomultiplier Tube" href="Photomultiplier_Tube">photomultiplier tube</a>s. A CCD scanner can either be color, grayscale, or black-and-white. CCD scanners use two CCD arrays, each possessing 2,048 photosites. Consequently, a total of 4,096 photosites can capture 4,096 pixels across each scan line. See <a title="CCD" class="nonexistent" href="http://printwiki.org/CCD">CCD</a> and <a title="CCD Array" href="CCD_Array">CCD Array</a>. 
</p>
